'''''Star Wars Annual'' 1''' is the first Annual issue in [[Star Wars (1977)|Marvel's ''Star Wars'']] series of comics.

This story was separated into two parts. Part 2 was titled "A Duel of Eagles!"

This issue includes a gallery of some of the covers of the British ''[[Star Wars Weekly]]''.

==Plot summary==
While [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] are on the planet [[Tirahnn/Legends|Tirahnn]] they are attacked by a group of [[Catuman]] warriors under the orders of [[Kharys]], the [[Magister of Skye|Majestrix]] of [[Skye/Legends|Skye]]. [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] recognizes the description of Kharys from his old smuggling days and decides to confront her on her home planet of Skye, but the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] is shot down over the planet by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]]. Luke and Leia are captured and brought to trial before the [[Supreme Council of the Highland Clans]], and there Leia is recognized as an enemy of the Empire but Luke is recognized as the son of their wingless brother and so the council decides to help the two [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]]. Meanwhile Han and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] have been captured by Kharys and questioned about what they know about Luke Skywalker. Luke and Leia along with their [[S'kytri]] allies attack the Majestrix's fortress and rescue Solo and his first mate. Kharys is killed in a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] duel with Luke freeing Skye from Imperial rule.

==Continuity==
In this issue [[Aragh]] says that, during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and two of his students saved Skye from destruction. He said one student was [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and the other he identified by saying [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] wore his [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]], implying it was Luke's father. As [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']] established that Vader ''was'' Luke's father, this implication turned out to be impossible. The discrepancy was first explained in [[Star Wars Gamer 1|''Star Wars Gamer'' 1]] and later expanded upon in 2007 in the article "[[Aliens in the Empire]]." The issue was also rectified in the [[2015]] story, [[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]].

During her duel with Luke, Kharys uses an ability that is similar to the stun/stasis Force power introduced in the [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic|''Knights of the Old Republic'']] video game.

In this issue, Han Solo states that it has been years since he saw [[Katya M'Buele|Katya M'Beule]]. ''[[Rebel Dawn]]'' mentions Katya as one of the smugglers who participated in the [[Battle of Ylesia]], which took place in the weeks leading up to the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. Thus Han's statement cannot be the case, as this comic is dated to [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]].

Following initial inconsistent publication dates, this tale is often collected between [[Star Wars (1977) 30|''Star Wars'' (1977) 30]] and [[Star Wars (1977) 31|''Star Wars'' (1977) 31]]. However, Han Solo and Chewbacca are still on [[Orleon]] at this time and do not reunite with Luke Skywalker until the events depicted in ''Return to Tatooine'', making this timeline placement impossible. A logical placement for this story is within the time gap in the early pages of [[Star Wars (1977) 35|''Star Wars'' (1977) 35]].

